reviewText: Our entire family loves this flick. Its a slapstick riot to be sure and the two Jims really make the movie. It boggles the mind that this hasnt seen a DVD release yet. I bet I could come up with a list of 1000 other flicks that are much less deserving, but yet we move on to blueray and Hi-Def with no release in sight for this comedy gem.  Maybe the execs in charge of this release are all "tankin up"  :<)

reviewText: "Hey baby, que paso?"UPDATE: This dvd has a very good picture, especially for a 1992 movie with a budget under 2 million. It is a huge improvement over the picture quality of the vhs tape. The sharp, colorful picture is in anamorphic widescreen 1.85:1. The video quality might possibly be just a little below the that of a recent high budget flick on dvd, but not by much. The improved picture alone makes buying this dvd well worth while, even if you already have the vhs tape.But the audio is something else. Not as clear as it could be, no improvement over the Hi-Fi tracks on my old vhs tape.Also, no subtitles or closed captions. Bummer.The five stars is for the movie, the video quality and the fact that dvds are better than vhs tapes. Take almost half a star off for so-so audio. I like subtitles or cc, but I don't need them, so nothing off for lack of either. YMMV in a big way with that one.Out On A Limb is a very funny movie with some fine actors. It has Matthew Broderick's trademark charm and wonderful smile. If you like the fellow at all, this is a must have movie. If you're indifferent to him, it's still a laugh inducing movie. Lots of humor, both deadpan and pratfall. It's also fairly kid friendly, if you don't mind one person getting shot dead and another who thought that they were about to die saying a four letter word for excrement. In my opinion, most kids who hang out with other kids already hear more cuss words more often than almost any adult. That was certainly true of me as a kid and every kid that I knew. We just didn't use those words in front of any adults as they tended to freak. But some adults seem to think a kid will drop dead or something if they as much as hear a word stronger than "darn". On the other hand, that kid might remind the parents who it was that bought/rented the movie with the naughty word and try to get away with saying that word every few seconds for years. Just because the kids don't drop dead doesn't mean that those kids won't try to annoy their parents to death.For more info on the movie, see the other reviews, especially EDMONTONROX's.
